                                "start": 0,
                                "stop": 5.954,
                                "byte_start": 77435,
                                "byte_stop": 101259,
                                "text": "The opinion for the Court in Number 80-1431 will be delivered by Justice Powell."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 5.954,
                        "stop": 161.298,
                        "byte_start": 101259,
                        "byte_stop": 722659,
                        "speaker": {
                            "ID": 15119,
                            "name": "Lewis F. Powell, Jr.",
                            "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/people\/lewis_f_powell_jr",
                            "last_name": "Powell",
                            "roles": [
                                {
                                    "id": 2764,
                                    "type": "scotus_justice",
                                    "date_start": 63612000,
                                    "date_end": 551682000,
                                    "appointing_president": "Richard Nixon",
                                    "role_title": "Associate Justice of the Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "institution_name": "Supreme Court of the United States",
                                    "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/preson_role\/scotus_justice\/2764"
                                }
                            ],
                            "thumbnail": {
                                "id": 32738,
                                "mime": "image\/png",
                                "size": 53543,
                                "href": "https:\/\/api.oyez.org\/sites\/default\/files\/lewis_f_powell_jr.png"
                            },
                            "length_of_service": 5649,
                            "identifier": "lewis_f_powell_jr"
                        },
                        "text_blocks": [
                            {
                                "start": 5.954,
                                "stop": 15.917,
                                "byte_start": 101259,
                                "byte_stop": 141174,
                                "text": "This case here on appeal from the Supreme Court of Missouri involves the validity of rules governing the advertisement by lawyers."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 15.917,
                                "stop": 28.681,
                                "byte_start": 141174,
                                "byte_stop": 192165,
                                "text": "State supreme courts, aided by the organized bar, adopt rules or Canons of Professional conduct that now include regulation of advertising."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 28.681,
                                "stop": 39.143,
                                "byte_start": 192165,
                                "byte_stop": 234065,
                                "text": "The Missouri rule had issue in this case specifies 10 categories of information that may be included in an advertisement."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 39.143,
                                "stop": 45.913,
                                "byte_start": 234065,
                                "byte_stop": 261128,
                                "text": "It limits the language that a lawyer may use in identifying the areas of his practice."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 45.913,
                                "stop": 58.799,
                                "byte_start": 261128,
                                "byte_stop": 312642,
                                "text": "And among other provisions, it allows the mailing of professional announcement cards only to lawyers, clients, former clients, personal friends and relatives."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 58.799,
                                "stop": 71.046,
                                "byte_start": 312642,
                                "byte_stop": 361647,
                                "text": "There also is a restriction against identifying oneself as a member of the Bar of this Court or of the Bar of another state."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 71.046,
                                "stop": 88.925,
                                "byte_start": 361647,
                                "byte_stop": 433223,
                                "text": "The Missouri Disciplinary Committee charged their lawyer with violation by the advertising that he published in telephone directory and by virtue of cost it was sent out by this lawyer."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 88.925,
                                "stop": 98.313,
                                "byte_start": 433223,
                                "byte_stop": 470735,
                                "text": "The Missouri Supreme Court agreed that there were violations of the rules and held however that the rules were perfectly valid."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 98.313,
                                "stop": 102.801,
                                "byte_start": 470735,
                                "byte_stop": 488707,
                                "text": "It issued a private reprimand for the violations."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 102.801,
                                "stop": 114.873,
                                "byte_start": 488707,
                                "byte_stop": 536981,
                                "text": "In Bates against Arizona, we held that advertising by lawyers is a form of commercial speech protected by the First and Fourteenth Amendments."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 114.873,
                                "stop": 120.777,
                                "byte_start": 536981,
                                "byte_stop": 560596,
                                "text": "We made clear however, that misleading advertisement is not protected."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 120.777,
                                "stop": 133.631,
                                "byte_start": 560596,
                                "byte_stop": 612005,
                                "text": "Moreover, we reiterate today that the potential for deception and confusion is particularly strong in the context of advertising for professional services."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 133.631,
                                "stop": 146.733,
                                "byte_start": 612005,
                                "byte_stop": 664459,
                                "text": "In this case, although the advertising violated the Missouri rules, there was no finding that it was inherently misleading or that the public had in fact been mislead."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 146.733,
                                "stop": 156.632,
                                "byte_start": 664459,
                                "byte_stop": 704060,
                                "text": "We conclude therefore that the Missouri rules, as applied in this case, cannot be squared with the Court\u2019s decision in Bates against Arizona."
                            },
                            {
                                "start": 156.632,
                                "stop": 161.298,
                                "byte_start": 704060,
                                "byte_stop": 722659,
                                "text": "Accordingly, we reverse the judgment of the Supreme Court of Missouri."
                            }
                        ]
                    },
